# Airline Handling System

A comprehensive airline management system built in C++ that handles flight operations, passenger bookings, crew management, and flight scheduling. Demonstrates advanced system design with real-world operational requirements.

## Features
- Flight schedule management
- Passenger booking system
- Crew assignment and tracking
- Airline fleet management
- Reservation processing
- Real-time availability checking
- Booking history and records

## Tech Stack
- **Language:** C++ (100%)
- **Data Structure:** Linked Lists, Queues, Arrays
- **Architecture:** Object-Oriented Design

## Project Structure
AirlineHandlingSystem/ ├── Flight Management # Flight scheduling and operations ├── Passenger System # Booking and reservation handling ├── Crew Management # Staff assignment and tracking ├── Fleet Operations # Aircraft management └── Reporting # System analytics and records


## Core Functionality
- Add/remove flights from schedule
- Book and manage passenger reservations
- Assign crew to flights
- Check flight availability
- Generate operation reports
- Manage seat allocation

## System Requirements
- C++ compiler
- Console environment
- 2MB+ storage

## Usage
Launch the application
Navigate through menu options
Book flights or manage operations
View schedules and reports
